{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 19:33:52.557484", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: Spine–leaf SDN with OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) and hosts (host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2). All switches managed by an OpenFlow controller at 20.0.0.100.\\n- Objective: Assess current network health, detect anomalies, localize faulty elements, and identify the likely root cause. No remediation is included.\\n\\nKey Symptoms and Tests\\n1) End-host reachability within and across leaves:\\n- host_1_1 → host_1_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n- host_2_1 → host_2_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n- host_1_1 ↔ host_2_1: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\nInterpretation: Even same-subnet peers on the same leaf cannot communicate.\\n\\n2) ARP on hosts:\\n- ip neigh on hosts shows entries marked “FAILED” for peers (no ARP resolution).\\nInterpretation: L2 forwarding/learning is not functioning; ARP requests are not being delivered.\\n\\n3) OVS controller status on switches:\\n- leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: fail_mode: secure\\n- ovs-vsctl list Controller shows is_connected: false with status last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633.\\n- ovs-ofctl dump-flows on all switches returns empty (no flows).\\nInterpretation: All switches are disconnected from the controller, and in secure mode drop all traffic when controller is down, leaving no dataplane learning or forwarding.\\n\\n4) Management network reachability:\\n- All switches can ping the controller IP 20.0.0.100 successfully (ICMP OK).\\nInterpretation: L3 connectivity to the controller host is fine; the refusal is at the TCP application port level (6633), not a reachability problem in the management network.\\n\\n5) Interface state/counters:\\n- Switch ports to hosts and inter-switch links are UP.\\n- Leaf ports RX some frames (e.g., ARP), but TX is 0, consistent with dropping in secure mode due to lack of controller flows.\\n\\nAnomaly Detection\\n- Severe network outage for data-plane traffic: complete loss of host-to-host connectivity and ARP failure.\\n- All OVS instances report controller connection refused and have empty flow tables while configured in fail_mode=secure.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Not a physical/link issue: interfaces are UP and management network works.\\n- Not a host configuration issue: hosts have valid IPs in the same /24 and attempt ARP.\\n- Fault lies at the SDN control plane boundary:\\n  - The OpenFlow controller endpoint 20.0.0.100:6633 is refusing TCP connections.\\n  - All switches are in secure mode and therefore drop traffic without controller-programmed flows.\\n\\nRoot Cause (Most Likely)\\n- The OpenFlow controller service at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting connections on TCP port 6633 (service not running, not listening on 6633, or actively refusing). As a result, all OVS switches are disconnected and, due to fail_mode=secure, are dropping all dataplane traffic. This directly explains the lack of ARP resolution and host communication failures., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='14cadffd-77a4-4d00-af85-bb433f3fe1f9'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
